UID:drJ1QKjVQ9ZgUxV8hcdsZ
SUMMARY:Youth Soapstone Carving Workshops At Best of the Northwest Art Show
DTSTAMP:20260406T030448Z
DTSTART:20260411T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Northwest Stone Sculptors Association \\(NWSSA\\) is excite
	d to offer Youth Soapstone Carving Workshops during the Northwest Art Alli
	ance Best of the Northwest Spring Show on April 11th & 12th at Magnuson Pa
	rk Hangar 30.\n\nYouth can participate an up-close\, hands-on experience w
	ith creativity by learning to carve their own soapstone animal figurine. A
	rtist instructors from the Northwest Stone Sculptors Association will guid
	e youth participants Ages 7 – 17 through the process of shaping this beaut
	iful\, natural material into a figurine to take home. These workshops are 
	designed to promote fine motor skills\, 3D spatial reasoning\, and artisti
	c confidence. The soapstone and all necessary kid-safe tools and water to 
	minimize dust will be provided.\n\nThe youth workshops are Free with admis
	sion to the Best of the Northwest Show.  \n\nTwo 90 minute sessions are av
	ailable\, on Saturday April 11th and Sunday\, April 12th beginning at 10:3
	0 am and 1:30 pm.  Spots are limited and registration is encouraged.\n\nht
	tps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/youth-soapstone-carving-worksh
	ops-at-best-of-the-northwest-art-show/18318379/2026-04-11T00\n\nFrom SEAto
